Release blockers:
  ☐ Path-dep versions for crates.io - `Cargo.toml [workspace.dependencies]` references `bevy-react-animations` / `bevy-react-canvas` / `bevy-react-macros` by `path` only. crates.io rejects path-only deps — each needs `version = "0.1.0"` alongside `path`, and the leaf crates must be published first (macros → canvas/animations → core).
  ☐ npm publish model - `js/package.json` `exports` ship raw `./src/*.ts` (no build output). Confirm that's intended for the esbuild-bundling consumer, or add a build step and ship compiled JS + `.d.ts`.
  ✔ add docs.rs - `[package.metadata.docs.rs]` (all-features + `--cfg docsrs`) on all six lib crates, `#![cfg_attr(docsrs, feature(doc_auto_cfg))]` in each `lib.rs` for cfg labels, and a docs.rs badge in `README.md`. Documents the default native target (rusty_v8 skips its V8 download when `DOCS_RS` is set, so no network needed); the wasm web-host module is left undocumented for now (would need `wasm32-unknown-unknown` in `targets` + the `getrandom_backend` rustflag, risking heavy-Bevy build timeouts). @done(26-06-30 16:44)
  ☐ Add `CHANGELOG.md` and `CONTRIBUTING.md`
  ☐ stabilize API

CI / correctness:
  ✔ Re-enable Rust bindings-drift check + test suite in `.github/workflows/ci.yml` (was commented out in `a131205` because linking OOM'd the runner). Fixed the OOM with the `mold` linker (apt) + `CARGO_PROFILE_DEV_DEBUG=0`, applied non-invasively via `mold -run <cmd>` on the `Test`/`Regenerate TS bindings` steps. Also corrected two stale names baked into the dead block: `gen:bindings`→`bevy:generate`, `generated.ts`→`bevy.ts`. @done(26-06-30)
